ral and political life, Chrostowska issues an urgent report on the vitality of utopia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aCritical theory. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aUtopias. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Utopias.2bisacsh  aBody Politics.  aBody Utopia.  aClimate Crisis.  aCritical Theory.  aHistory of Political Ideas (20th Century to the Present).  aRadical Political Thought.  aRadical Social Theory.  aUtopianism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363000040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503630000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503630000/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles